Students acquire an integrated overview of the project cycle and an introduction to project management and the log matrix method. Activities supporting the implementation of projects, such as team selection and communication are briefly treated.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The student acquires the management and financing of social projects, basic knowledge and practical skills in project design.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows project cycle methodology and different phases; 2) knows EU structural funds financing principles; 3) can carry out and manage the strategic planning of the project; 4) knows, how to design the project budget; 5) uses professional terminology.
